title: Kendall Jenner Rocked a Runway Look to the 2019 Emmys, and People Loved It
text:
Making a surprise appearance as a presenter at tonight's Emmy Awards, Kendall Jenner rocked a fresh-off-the-runway look, straight out of Richard Quinn's Spring 2020 collection.

Kendall presented the award for the 'Outstanding Competition Program’ alongside her sister, Kim, wearing a shiny, latex-looking long sleeve mock turtleneck underneath the fitted floral gown with rose print. The look was identical to that of the runway model from the designer's London Fashion Week show, which took place last week.

Her hair was pulled back, slick and parted in the middle and her chunky diamond studs added just the right amount of sparkle to the ensemble.

71st Emmy Awards - Executive Arrivals Alberto E. Rodriguez More

Kendall has just returned from Milan Fashion Week, where she rocked blonde locks in the Versace show, and also walked for Fendi. She was notably absent from New York Fashion week, though, deciding to take a break.

She explained to E! News, "It's a lot more mellow to just go [to NYFW]." She added, "but I won't lie, today I was missing it. I was watching the girls and I was like, 'Damn, I kind of want to walk.'"

Her runway-to-Emmy's look was one of the more bold ensembles of the evening. Check out all the purple carpet fashion, here.

Originally Appeared on Teen Vogue
description: The model took a break from Fashion Month to present an award alongside her sister, Kim.
